    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - ROCKWELL TANDEM AXLE FORWARD REAR DRIVE UNITS - ASSEMBLE -
        OUTPUT BEARINGS AND OUTPUT SHAFT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>OUTPUT BEARINGS AND OUTPUT SHAFT</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f14011b2">Figure 112</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f14011b2" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg14/G14011B2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="150"/>
            <caption>Figure 112. Output Bearings and Output Shaft</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. OUTPUT SHAFT</callout1>
                <callout1>2. BEARING ASSEMBLIES</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SNAP RING</callout1>
                <callout1>4. OUTPUT YOKE</callout1>
                <callout1>5. OIL SEAL</callout1>
                <callout1>6. SPACER</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the bearing cups and the cones with axle lubricant. Refer to GROUP 10 -
                LUBRICATION in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If the bearing cone is replaced, the bearing cup must also be replaced. Replace the cup and the
                    cone in a matched set from the same manufacturer.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>Observe all warnings and cautions concerning press operation to avoid serious personal injury and
                    possible damage to components.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the bearing cones were removed from the through shaft, install new bearing cones. Put
                both cones back-to-back on the through shaft. Use a press and a sleeve to install both cones. Apply
                pressure until the inner cone seats on the shoulder of the through shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f14011b3">Figure 113</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f14011b3" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg14/G14011B3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="150"/>
            <caption>Figure 113. Use Press and Sleeve to Install Bearing Cones</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a press and a sleeve to install the inner bearing cup in the cage. Put the output shaft
                and bearing assembly in the cage.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a press and a sleeve to install the outer bearing cup into the cage over the output
                shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f14011b4">Figure 114</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f14011b4" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg14/G14011B4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="150"/>
            <caption>Figure 114. Install Outer Bearing Cup</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. CAGE</callout1>
                <callout1>2. PRESS</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SLEEVE</callout1>
                <callout1>4. OUTER BEARING CUP</callout1>
                <callout1>5. OUTER BEARING CONE</callout1>
                <callout1>6. INNER BEARING CUP</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the snap ring that fastens the outer cup in the cage. The snap ring controls the end
                play of the output bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f14011b5">Figure 115</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f14011b5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg14/G14011B5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="150"/>
            <caption>Figure 115. Install Snap Ring</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. BEARING CAGE</callout1>
                <callout1>2. SNAP RING</callout1>
                <callout1>3. OUTPUT SHAFT</callout1>
                <callout1>4. END VIEW</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the snap ring (yoke-to-cone spacer) on the output shaft until the snap ring touches
                the outer cone.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check and adjust the end play of the output bearing.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
